      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>Format for the citation of the described materials that is preferred by the
                  custodian.
      </p>
      <p>When multiple citation formats exist for the same item, each is recorded in a separate
                     occurrence of field 524.
      </p>
      <p>The note is sometimes displayed and/or printed with an introductory phrase that is
                     generated as a display constant based on the first indicator value.      </p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> INDICATORS
      </h4>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>First Indicator - Display constant controller</strong> <div class="description">Controls the generation of a display constant preceding the note.
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong># - Cite as</strong> <div class="description">Used to generate the display constant <em>Cite as:</em>.
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>8 - No display constant generated</strong> </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>Second Indicator - Undefined</strong> <div class="description">Undefined and contains a blank (#).
            </div>
      </div>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> SUBFIELD CODES
      </h4>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$a - Preferred citation of described materials note</strong> <div class="description">Entire text of the note.</div>
         <div class="example">
