      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$3 - Materials specified</strong> <div class="description">Part of the described materials to which the field applies.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
        <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
        </div>
   </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Punctuation</strong> - Field 524 ends with a period unless another mark of punctuation is present.
      </div>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Display Constant</strong> - Introductory phrase <em>Cite as:</em> is not carried in the MARC record. It may be
                     system generated as a display constant associated with the first indicator value.
         <div class="table">
            <table>
               <tr>
                  <td width="124" align="left" valign="top"><u>First indicator</u></td>
                  <td width="298" align="left" valign="top"><u>Display constant</u></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">#</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Cite as:</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">8</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left"><em>[no display constant]</em></td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
